<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1423" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1423">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.42/325.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi><note n="124" xml:id="d1423fn124">Communicated to the Spanish
                                    Ambassador June 19, 1914.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-13">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s June 8. Spanish Vice Consul in the name of Spanish
                                colony yesterday requested me to request State Department to take no
                                further action on the question of enforced loans and stated that
                                payments which have been made were voluntary and that Spaniards have
                                made no complaint. Governor General Caballero has distributed
                                circulars calling a meeting of Spanish colony at Governor’s palace
                                for next Sunday morning.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>